Kenya on Saturday reported  29, 849 Covid-19 cases after 515 more people tested positive. This was out of  6,363 samples tested in at least 24 hrs. Health CAS Dr Mercy Mwangangi said out of the total cases, 496 are Kenyans while 19 are foreigners. Mwangangi said the youngest is an 8 months old infant while the oldest is 96 year old. She said some 672 other patients had been discharged bringing the number of total recoveries to 15,970. "Out of this number 55 have been discharged from various health facilities across the country while 607 are from the home-based care programme," she said. Mwangangi said unfortunately 7 more patients had succumbed bringing the total number of fatalities to 472. More to follow....